cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a framework for online motion planning and adaptation for autonomous robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The framework is based on a bio-inspired stochastic recurrent neural network, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of learning signals and mental replay strategy also suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the evaluation of the framework on an anthropomorphic arm involves computer vision (cs.CV) for tracking the arm's motion.
